│ the user `U` is a `BranchInst`. If it is, we should not proceed to check its type size. Since a branch instruction doesn't produce a value that would be part of a  │
│ data-dependency chain in the way SLP is concerned with (i.e., widening types), it's safe to consider it "not safe to speculate" in this context, or at least to     │
