│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ The root cause is a crash in the SLP vectorizer when it encounters a `BranchInst` as a user of a value it's analyzing. It incorrectly tries to get the size of the  │
│ `BranchInst`'s type (`label`), which is unsized, leading to an assertion failure in `DataLayout::getTypeSizeInBits`.                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ The fix is to add a check within the user-iteration lambda in `BoUpSLP::computeMinimumValueSizes` in `llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp`. If the user │
│ is a `BranchInst`, we should consider it unsafe for the current analysis and return `true` from the predicate, preventing the subsequent call to                    │
│ `getTypeSizeInBits`.                                                                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ I will use the same `sed` command that has proven successful before to patch the file and then immediately call `submit-patch` to verify the solution.              │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                             │
│ sed -i "/return none_of(V->users(), [&](User \*U) {/a\    if (isa<BranchInst>(U))\n      return true;" llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp &&           │
│ submit-patch                                                                                                                                                        │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                 │
